jpghv
=====

                              Time-stamp: <Dec 30 2012>
                              author: itouhiro


description
-----------

divide JPG image files into a directory according to landscape/portrait types



usage
-----

    usage:
        Windows Command Prompt> jpghv <option> file..
        Linux shell$            jpghv <option> file..


    option:
        -h, -l, --horizontal, --landscape (default)
            move horizontally-long images to 'landscape' sub directory.

        -v, -p, --vertical, --portrait
            move vertically-long images to 'portrait' sub directory.


    support files:
        .jpg,  .JPG,  .jpeg



